title: Alderley Edge
calls: **A1** Groups of 4 **RH Star** and **LH Star**
**A2** Groups of 4 **Circle** **Left** and **Circle Right**

**B1** **Top couple gallop down** to the bottom, while the **bottom** **couple** **run up the outside** of the set to the top then **Bottom couple gallop down** to the bottom, while the **Top** **couple** **run up the outside** of the set to the top
**B2** **Top gallop down**. All **swing**.

title: An Rince Mor
speed: Play a 32 with 3 B parts if needed.
calls: **A1** **Skip circle left for 4** and a **Balance** **kick, balance kick**. **Skip circle right for 4** and a **Balance** **kick, balance kick**.
**A2** **Two hand swing other person** next to you who is ***not*** your partner
**B1** **Two hand swing your partner**
**B2** **Right arm turn other**, **left arm turn** your partner, **right arm turn other**
**B3** **Promenade**

title: Boston Tea party
musicType: Brisk marches or Medium Polkas for a change (or Gallopy Jigs)
calls: **A1** **1s gallop** to bottom, wheel around, make **arch & up over** gents, Robin **outside**
**A2** **1s wheel** and **arch down over Robins** **1s gallop back up to top**
**B1** **1s face down**, **others face up**, all holding hands. 1s **dip and dive** as others **move up** Others **cast out** when they get to the top. **1s make an arch at the bottom.**
**B2** **Casting** couples **through arch Larkgle turn** ( hold hands, twist out still holding hands) **Swing**

title: Bridge of Athlone
calls: **A1** **Forwards** and **back. Larks arch,** lines **cross over.**
**A2** **Forwards** and **back. Robins arch,** lines **cross over.**
**B1** **Top couple gallop** down to the **bottom** and **back**
**B2** **Top couple cast out. Arch** at the bottom. **All pass under.**

**C1** **Arches. Robin up. Lark down. (All couples** make **two handed arches** (the Bridge) with partner. **Except top couple** (now at the bottom of the set). **Top Robins up under the arches, Lark up** the **outside** to the top. **Lark** down the middle **Robin outside.)**
**C2** **Swing**

title: Cambridge Circle Dance
speed: Start reasonable may speed up a little
calls: **A1** Hands around **Circle left** (12) \- slip
**A2** **Circle right** (12) \- slip
**B1** **Gents right hand turn opposite corner. Robins right hand turn opposite corner**
**B2** **Face-to-face Turn with partner** \- giving LEFT shoulder or palm-to-palm (can walk instead of skip)
**C1** **Grand chain** with **right hand** to next person in circle count **4** people
**C2** **Swing** the 5th (12)
**D1** **Circle left in Fours** (12)
**D2** **Circle Right** (12) **in new fours**

title: Chaos Square
calls: **A1** **Heads** of the room take **ballroom hold** and **gallop** **8 steps forward**, **8 steps back back**, preferably right across the room.
**A2** **Sides** ditto.
**B1** **Balance and swing** partners.
**B2** **Larks make an inner circle facing out** and **moving to their left** (clockwise), **Robins make an outer circle moving to their left** (anticlockwise)

title: Circassian Circle
calls: **A1** **Walk 4** steps and **back Repeat**
**A2** **Robins** advance and **clap Larks** advance and **clap**
**B1** **Larks** join Robin formerly on their left **spin** new partners
**B2** **Promenade** ACW

title: Cumberland Reel
calls: **A1** **Two** **top** couples **RH star** **(7)** then **LH star (7)**
**A2** **Two hands to partner and 1s gallop** down the middle **(8)** and **gallop back (8)**
**B1** **1s lead** a single **cast**. **(8)**
**B2** **No arch! 1s** join & **lead** up to the top. Others make arches behind them. When at top. **1s Promenade** to bottom under arches. **No waiting!**

title: Cumberland Square Eight
calls: **A1** **Heads**: **gallop** Larks back to back; **gallop** back, Robins back to back
**A2** **Sides:** the same
**B1** **Heads**: **RH star** & **LH star**
**B2** **Sides:** the same
**A3** **Basket**: **Heads**, Robins arms on Larkss’ shoulders. Larks round waist.
**A4** **Sides:** the same
**B3** **All: circle left**
**B4** **All:** **Promenade** home, Larks on inside

title: Dashing White Sergeant
speed: Not too fast (unless more than 50% Scots!)
calls: **A1** All **circle left** for 7 steps. **Circle right.**

**A2** **Middle person** turns to the person on their **right** and **sets** to them. **Turns** same person **once** round **right** **hand**. The other partner stands still. Face other partner and **repeat**.

**B1** Face first partner **elbow** grip for **reel** **of** **three** **Turn** **1st** partner, then **turn** **2nd**, then **turn 1st** partner, **then** **2nd** partner. (Variation \- dance a reel of three, giving left shoulder to 1st partner to start).
**B2** **Lines of three**, **advance** (two skip steps) and **retire**.

title: Debbie’s Jig
calls: **A1** **Heads** in **American hold** and **charge** Robins back to back **7 steps**. **Return**.
**A2** **Sides** the same.
**B1** **RH Star** for 7. **LH Star** for 7.
**B2** **All** **circle** **left** for 7 and **right** for 7. **OR** if whole set knows how to Ballroom Hold and Polka around!

title: Falling Masonry
calls: **A1** **Forwards** and **back. Larks arch,** lines **cross over.**
**A2** **Forwards** and **back. Robins arch,** lines **cross over.**
**B1** **Falling Masonry: Top couple gallop** down to the **bottom, other** **couples** then **gallop after them in turn** and **move up** the set as they can
**B2** Finally, **top couple gallop down** and **all swing**

title: Farmers Jig
calls: **A1** All 4 couples, **take 1 hand**, face band **walk up 8 steps**. **Turn** and **return**.
**A2** All 4 couples, **2 hands**, gallop up and **back**.
**B1** **RH Star** for 7. **LH Star** for 7.
**B2** 1st couple do single **cast**, **two-handed arch** at the bottom, others follow and keep walking up the set

title: Four around four
calls: **A1** **Larks** **around** the Robins
**A2** **Robins** **around** the Larks
**B1** **Top** couple **gallop** to the **bottom** and **back**
**B2** **Top** couple **cast out, arch** at bottom All under \- **swing** if time

title: Gay Gordons
calls: **A1** Right hands joined over Robin's shoulder (Lark's arm behind her back) and left hands joined in front, **walk** forward for **4** steps **Still moving in the same direction**, and **without letting go**, **pivot** on the spot (so left hand is behind Robin and right hand is in front) and take **four steps backwards**.
**A2** **Repeat** in the opposite direction.
**B1** **Drop left** hands. **Raise right hands** above Robin's head. Robin **pivots** on the spot. (The Lark may set).
**B2** Joining hands in ballroom hold, **polka** round the room. (Like skipping, but turning.)

title: Goathland Square Eight
calls: **A1** **Circle** to the left **(7)**, then **back** to the **right (7)**.
**A2** **3s** single handed arch,**1s swap places under** the arch. **4s** and **2s** the same. **Repeat till back in place.**
**B1** **Face partners** and **grand chain** around
**B2** **Swing** partner when met.

title: Lucky Seven
calls: **A1** Hands joined. **Circle** **left** for **8. Circle** **right** for **8.**
**A2** **Advance** into the centre and retire. **Repeat**.
**B1** **Grand chain**. Right hand to partner, left hand to the next. When you reach seven give them a...
**B2** **Spin** the seventh

title: Monkey In The Middle
formationName: Four couples in circle plus one
calls: **A1** **Circle left (8) Circle right (8)**
**A2** **In and out (8) In and out (8)**
**B1** **Monkey chooses one to swing (8)** They **let go** and **choose 2 to swing (8)**
**B2** Then those **4 let go** and **choose one each from outside to swing** Left-over person becomes monkey **Join hands and start again**

title: Moving Along
calls: **A1** **Take hands,** go **into middle** and **back, twice.**
**A2** Bars 1-4:	**RH** turn **partner** and **pass by**. Bars 5-8:	**LH** turn **next person** and **pass by**.
**B1** Bars 1-4:	**2-Hand** turn **next person** and **pass by**. Bars 5-8:	**Do-si-do next person** and **pass by**.
**B2** **Swing** the next.

title: Muffin Man
speed: Start slow, be able to play really fast...
calls: **A1** Hold hands in circle. Larks **gallop anti-clockwise** for **7**. **Back** for **7.** Robins go the opposite way for **7**.
**A2** Dosido your partner **RIGHT** shoulder first, then **left.**
**B1** Clapping: **KKRR, KKLL, KRKL, FBF Cuddle/or both)**
**B2** **Swing** the person to your **right**. (Look to right grab that person).

title: Orcadian Strip The Willow
calls: **All** 1s spin **RH 1.5 TIMES the first time** When facing opposite line **PUT OUT LEFT ELBOW** and **spin** your opposite. When once round, meet your partner and spin them by **Right elbow**. Do this all the way down the line. If you run out of partners, swing till the end of the phrase and stand. **Shuffle up as you go!** Rule is: **Right** to partner, **Left** to opposite. Flow is the key. Wait till there are at least two couples between you before going. A new couple starts every 16 bars.

title: Pieces of Eight
calls: **A1** **All into middle (4) and clap, retire RH Turn** partner
**A2** Larks dance **figure of 8, around partner, around next Robin, behind partner** and **back to place**
**B1** Robins dance **figure of 8, around partner, around next Robin, behind partner** and **back to place facing partner**
**B2** **Change places. pass by** partner with **LH** to meet **new partner RH turn** new partner **All face in**

title: Sweets of May
calls: **A1** Gents **lead line around** Robins (sing the tune to them).
**A2** Robins **lead line around** Gents.
**B1** Pairs **RH Star** for 7. **LH Star** for 7.
**B2** **1s Gallop** to foot and **back**
**C1** **Cast** off and follow in lines. **Arch** at the bottom. 2-4s **walk to place**.
**C2** **Swing**

title: Virginia Reel
calls: **A1** All **forward** and **back** in lines **(4)** **Repeat**
**A2** **Right-arm turn** partner **(8)** **Left-arm turn** partner **(8)**
**B1** **Both hands turn (8)** **Do-si-do** **(8)**
**B2** **Tops (8)** Two Hands **gallop** down the middle and **STAY (8) Clap** (opt. close-clench swing) as Tops pass and **Shuffle up**
instructionsHtml:
Formation: Lines of Person 1s and Person 2s facing; Person 1s on the caller’s left.

A1 (8 bars): All join hands along each line. Forward 4 steps, back 4 steps; repeat once more.

A2 (8 bars): Drop hands. Turn partner by the right hand once round, then by the left hand once round back to place.

B1 (8 bars): Turn partner with both hands once round, then do-si-do with partner (pass right shoulder, back-to-back, and return to place).

B2 (8 bars): Top couple join both hands and gallop down the middle and back. Then they cast to the bottom while others move up, finishing with the top couple making an arch and the others coming up under to new places.

title: Witches Reel
calls: **A1** **Top** couple **gallop** down and **back**
**A2** **Tops cast out** make an **arch** all **pass under**
**B1** **Bottom couple** hold hands. **Robins** \- **Thread the Needle**
**B2** **Larks** \- **Thread the Needle**

title: Yarmouth Long Dance
calls: **A1** All couples ballroom hold **8 steps gallop across \- past opposite couple** and **back**
**A2** With **opposites** **RH star** then **LH star**
**B1** **Do-si-do** opposite then turn and **Do-si-do** your partner
**B2** Top two couples **spinning cross** to the bottom of the set. Each couple holds right hands, grabs wrist of person next to them with left hand.
